&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ward Manager - Orthopaedic Trauma&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Following a reconfiguration of Orthopaedic services with RLUBHT, a vacancy has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated Ward Manager within Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics. You will have a passion for quality and safety and the drive and commitment to aim to get it right for every patient every time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trauma and Orthopaedics is a fast paced, busy, acute inpatient speciality within the Aintree site. The bed base contains 3 Wards, including the Acute Femoral Fracture Unit (AFFU) based on Ward 1, and Trauma and Orthopaedics based on Ward&#39;s 3 and 16.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You should be a Registered Nurse with a minimum of 2 years acute experience setting at Band 6, with Orthopaedic/Surgical experience. You should have a keen interest in providing high quality, harm free, patient centred care in a busy, fast paced, ever changing and often challenging environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For this role you will need to demonstrate excellent communication skills and possess the ability to lead the team effectively. As a Ward Manager you must display a positive and professional manner, have a non-judgmental attitude, and be open to change.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return you will receive support to develop personally and professionally and gain invaluable leadership and management experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
